column1: Cold water- first really warm day of spring.  The Loons have stopped in on their way north.  DO probe on meter not working
One Loon observed.  Hopefully- the hen is nesting in the wet land area.  A pair of American Bitterns observed.

column2: Sunny- light breeze.  2 mute swans observed.  light (2 boats) boat traffic.
With Zoe McManama on sampling quality audit
Loons have been stopping by for the past two weeks

column1: Lake turned over and beginning to stratify
Today:  P cloudy- 15mph wind- Grt Blue Heron- gills are going on beds- great water clarity- water is warmer than the air today.  Wife Mary paddled and recorded.

column2: Greenish cast to water.  Slight algae bloom occured 2 days prior.  Rain 1/2" 3 days prior.  Camps are in opereation.  Boating activity picking up with fishermen and water sports.
